#107
SYSLOG RUSAGE

   The syslog rusage lines provide system resource usage information that
appears periodically in the system log (every 5 minutes). This information 
is only visible to immortals level LVL_GRGOD and above.

   Two rusage entries are logged:
   
   1. Delta usage - CPU time used since the last measurement:
      - Shows performance spikes and recent activity impact
      - Positive values indicate CPU usage, zero means no usage
      - Helps identify bottlenecks and performance issues
      
   2. Total usage - Cumulative CPU time since server start:
      - User time: CPU time spent executing user code (in seconds)
      - System time: CPU time spent in system calls (in seconds)  
      - Max res size: Maximum resident set size (memory usage)

   This information helps monitor server performance and identify when
resource usage spikes occur. The delta values are particularly useful
for detecting performance bottlenecks that could lead to missed pulses.

Example log entries:
   rusage delta: user: +2 sec, system: +0 sec
   rusage total: user time: 47 sec, system time: 12 sec, max res size: 524288

